title: Possible Suspect - Alone in the Fight (Punk, 1998) (FLAC)
description:
1998 demo tape by Dutch anarcho-punk band Possible Suspect.

This is a compact cassette rip, type II with no Dolby noise reduction. The recording quality is what you'd expect of a 90s punk band. Still, the tracks are losslessly compressed FLACs - if there's someone out there who knows how to do proper noise reduction and equalisation to get these songs up to spec, I look forward to your torrent! For everyone else: you are encouraged to embrace the warm, friendly hiss of the tape.

The Possible Suspects were:
Esther (drums)
Iwan (guitar)
Dick (guitar)
Wander (bass)
Mark (voice)

More info can be found in the included scan of the cassette's J-card, which, incidentally, lists the song "Depression" among the tracks, though it is not present on the tape.

1 Alone in the Fight
2 My Own D
3 Exclosure of Humankind
4 Read God's Word Everyday
5 I Don't Wanna Be With You
6 Complain
